paragraphs.text:
%spark
import org.apache.spark.sql.types._
import org.apache.spark.sql.functions._
import com.knockdata.spark.highcharts._
import com.knockdata.spark.highcharts.model._


val testcaseSchema = StructType(Array(
    StructField("buildTimestamp", StringType, nullable=true),
    StructField("testCaseStatus", StringType, nullable=true),
    StructField("duration", DoubleType, nullable=true),
    StructField("buildNumber", IntegerType, nullable=true),
    StructField("builtOn", StringType, nullable=true),
    StructField("sut", StringType, nullable=true),
    StructField("jobName", StringType, nullable=true),
    StructField("className", StringType, nullable=true),
    StructField("testCaseName", StringType, nullable=true)
  ))
    
    
val testcaseFile = "/usr/zeppelin/data/apache-jenkins-data/testCase.csv.gz"

val apacheTestcaseCompleteDF = sqlContext.read.format("com.databricks.spark.csv").
    option("header", "false").option("mode", "DROPMALFORMED").
    schema(testcaseSchema).load(testcaseFile).cache
apacheTestcaseCompleteDF.first

paragraphs.title: Max Sum Execution Duration TestCases Histogram
Max Sum Execution Duration TestCases Drilldown
paragraphs.text:
highcharts(apacheTestcaseDF.series(
        "name" -> "testCaseStatus",
        "y" -> count("testCaseStatus")).
    drilldown(
        "name" -> "testCaseName",
        "y" -> sum($"duration")).
    orderBy(sum($"duration").desc).
    take(50)
    ).plotOptions(PlotOptions.column.groupPadding(0).pointPadding(0).borderWidth(0)).
    chart(Chart.column).plot
